alert.note: Alert for Coastal Levy; Inland Levy (Florida) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Special Weather Statement issued June 17 at 8:59AM EDT by NWS Tampa Bay
info.description: ...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of Levy County through 945 AM EDT... At 858 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along a line extending from 8 miles east of Trenton to 6 miles east of Chiefland to 9 miles southeast of Fowlers Bluff. Movement was east at 15 mph. HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph. SOURCE...Radar indicated. IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around unsecured objects. Locations impacted include... Williston, Chiefland, Bronson, Williston Highlands, East Bronson, Andrews, Williston Municipal Airport, Manattee Road, Fowlers Bluff, Fanning Springs, Otter Creek, Manatee Springs State Park, and Lebanon. MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH
info.instruction: If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building. Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.
